team.cascade.spout.makememod.helper.config
Class Configuration

Object
  CommentConfiguration
      Configuration

public class Configuration
extends CommentConfiguration

Here you will find all the information you will normally want to change to your liking. If you make changes to the CONFIG enums increase the configCurrent number and the plugin will handle autoupdating if configured.

The following is the default configuration of the plugin if you don't change it via the corresponding setters or the enums TILL the config is loaded:

  • configFile = config.yml
  • debugLogEnabled = false
  • debugLogToFile = true
  • checkForUpdate = true
  • configAutoUpdate = true
  • configAutoSave = true
  • configLogEnabled = true
  • disableOnOlderBuilds = false

Version:

Author:
$Author: dredhorse$

Field Summary
(package private)  String configCurrent
          This is the internal config version, which is being used if no Version is supplied from the plugin itself use CommentConfiguration.alterConfigCurrent(String conCurr) for this
(package private)  String pluginSlug
          Link to the location of the plugin website Note: This can be overwritten by CommentConfiguration.alterPluginSlug(String plugSlug)
(package private)  String versionURL
          Link to the location of the recent version number, the file should be a text with <version> x.y.rb-Bb for example your pom.yml
For a better explanation of the version number scheme please look here: Wiki
For those people who are interested what the version number means, e.g 3.5.1597-20
x.y.rb-Bb

x = Major Version = Major new stuff or internal rework
y = Minor Version = Minor new stuff and bug fixes
rb = Recommended Build of Spout
b = Development Build Version = if you have development builds for example B7
